OL,3,CEnd 'ridiculous' royal tax breaks,
OL,4,CGreens urge in election pledge
OL,6,FWhile most of these are reserved to
OL,7,Fthe UK Government, Land and Buildings
OL,8,FTransaction Tax (LBTT), called stamp
OL,9,Fduty in England, is fully devolved to
OL,10,Fthe Scottish Government.
OL,12,FMany people pay the tax when buying a
OL,13,Fhouse but the King would not because
OL,14,Ftransactions involving the Crown are
OL,15,Fexempt from LBTT.
OL,17,FThe Scottish Greens said they were
OL,18,Fcommitted to ending the exemption and
OL,19,F"making one of the country's biggest
OL,20,Flandowners pay his fair share".
OL,26,@{D@AOU|D@^O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
