PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775001769
OL,3,CEnd 'ridiculous' royal tax breaks,
OL,4,CGreens urge in election pledge
OL,6,FMr Greer said: "With costs soaring and
OL,7,Fpeople being priced out of everyday
OL,8,Fessentials, it is ridiculous that so
OL,9,Fmuch public money is given to one
OL,10,Fsuper-rich and scandal-ridden family
OL,11,Fbased on who their ancestors were.
OL,13,F"The King is one of the richest men in
OL,14,Fthe world and one of the biggest
OL,15,Flandowners in Scotland.
OL,17,F"He doesn't need even more perks, and
OL,18,Fhe shouldn't be given a free pass from
OL,19,Fpaying taxes simply because of the
OL,20,Fwealthy family he was born into."
OL,26,@nD@POUuD@AOUyD@AOU|D@aO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775001769
OL,3,CEnd 'ridiculous' royal tax breaks,
OL,4,CGreens urge in election pledge
OL,6,FMr Greer said it was unfair to have
OL,7,F"one rule for the elites" and "another
OL,8,Ffor the rest of us".
OL,10,FHe added: "Scotland should not be a
OL,11,Fnation where the powerful and
OL,12,Fprivileged are exempt from
OL,13,Fcontributing fairly.
OL,15,F"Even those who support having an
OL,16,Funelected head of state would surely
OL,17,Fagree that the King can afford to pay
OL,18,Ftowards our public services.
OL,26,@oD@AOUoD@YO]oD@_OUpD@SO]rD@KOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775001769
OL,3,CEnd 'ridiculous' royal tax breaks,
OL,4,CGreens urge in election pledge
OL,6,F"The monarchy is an anti-democratic
OL,7,Fhangover from an earlier era, and one
OL,8,Fthat the Scottish Greens would abolish
OL,9,Fin a heartbeat.
OL,11,F"Over the last few years the shocking
OL,12,Fscandals surrounding Andrew
OL,13,FMountbatten-Windsor in particular have
OL,14,Funderlined how poorly served we are by
OL,15,Fthem.
OL,17,F"No family should be allowed to exempt
OL,18,Fitself from following the law, but in
OL,19,Fso many ways that's exactly what the
OL,20,FWindsors do. It is long past time for
OL,21,Fthe King to start paying his taxes."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUyD@AOU}D@dO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
